content.message: Hello, How are you? Do you like google?
Hello, I am good. How are you? I do like google.  I use it so much every day that it is hard to believe it's been around since 1998. It seems like it's always been around.
I know, I use it alot too! its always there to go to!
Yes it is.  Larry Page and Sergey Brin have to be geniuses for thinking it up.
Agree, One single Google search requires a huge amount of computing power.
That is amazing to think about.  Do you know how much power it uses?
More than for Neil Armstrong and 11 astronauts to the moon!
Wow!  I had no idea it was that much.  So many people use google nowadays.  When it went down back in 2013 for five minutes it took %40 of web traffic with it.
That's scary! They had a good idea to use goats instead of a mowers.
What did they use the goats for?
Instead of mowing the lawn, they eat the grass at the headquarters.
I'm really impressed with that.  That sounds like they care about the environment.
Yes, you see that alot in Europe too!
Nice.  Europe, makes me think about how google does their maps.  If there is a border dispute they tailor it to the claims of each country where the browser is located.
Yes, I know. Hard to believe red and blue colors started  for both parties in 2000.
Are you talking about the political parties?  I thought those colors had been around much longer than that!
Yes, Thats what surprised me too! At least that what I always saw.
The parties have been around for a while. There hasn't been a president that hasn't been republican or democrat since 1853.
Yes, Republicans were the only party that had presidents with beards. lol Great chat!!
Harry Truman hated republicans so much he wouldn't even be photographed with Dumbo at Disneyland!
lol, I know, crazy! Good to be tall to win the election. They win most of the time.
Are you an avid reader?
I read about two books a week. Usually murder mysteries
Reading helps to exercise the cognitive skills.
I did so much reading in college that was textbook that I only read for pleasure now.
Same here. I do wish that I would have learned to read Braille.
I would like to have that skill. I think they should teach the basics in school.
Have you read Starship Troopers before?
I have not. I don't know what it is about. I like all the Classics, though. I would like to write.
I believe its a Sci-Fi and require reading for the military.
I will have to read it. In the 18th century they were worried about people reading too many novels! I think they used to call them 'penny dreadfuls' because they were cheap.
I can read almost as fast as the world record, i can read about 400 wpm
That's really good. I like to read slow so I don't have to keep going to the library.
DO you prefer hard copy books or do you read on your computer too?
I like to have a real book. I don't like to read on the computer at all. I think it's funny that someone built a computer from minecraft blocks.
I find it hard to believe the russians built a computer that runs on water.
I can't imagine that. I love my computer but I am glad I don't have to water it. lol
Very true. I enjoy watching movies on my computer while smoking.
If it is an Apple computer that will void the warranty. No smoking!
Uh oh, I did not know that. Is it a biohazard or something?
Yes, it is. I never knew that. I don't smoke but I have seen people smoke while using the computer. They are working on a way to upload your mind to the computer. I don't think I would do that!
I am going to go water my computer now.
Are you an NBA fan?
Yes I watch NBA games from time to time, what do you think about Stephen Curry in the Warriors?
He is a class act. I love the warriors!
Yeah he's awesome! How do you think they're going to do this year? Apparently the Wizards dont think they are going to do well
I don't think they will go all the way, they have had their ups and downs! I may be with the wizards on this one, what do you think
I don't know if Stephen Curry is pretty awesome LOL. How often do you watch the NBA though
I watch every night is on, I am watching the  warriors now ha. they are losing though, how about you
I watch it sometimes. I like the old guys like Michael Jordan he was my favorite, I especially liked his Air Jordan shoes
Me too, I like how Jordan wore his shoes even though he got fined by the NBA. I think nike paid his  fines
Yeah they did that was great advertising! What do you think about shooting a basketball granny style by the way
I heard it is effective but definitely silly looking, your thoughts?
It's definitely silly but physicists say it's the best way to shoot the ball lol so I think players should use it just because they are getting paid so much they can afford to look silly
Hmm I will have to work on my game! Were you a fan of tim duncan?
Yeah I like Tim Duncan, I was shocked that he didn't jump right into the NBA and instead stayed to finish his degree
I think it was his grandmas dying wish, it was a great thing he did
Oh wow I didn't know that. I also didn't know that Allen Iverson makes so much money from the Reebok sponsorship, $800,000 per year
Last I heard he was broke! I think he is getting a big chunk of money at 55
Yep he just has to hold out until age 55 and then he's going to get 32 million dollars, I think that should solve all his money problems lol
Lets hope lol, he doesnt have more after that! Good chatting with you!
Yep that would be a lot of debt haha. By the way what do you think about Stephen Curry? Apparently he plays with his brother Seth Curry
He is not as good as Steph though!
Hello, How are you? Are you interested in the planets?
You know, I used to be when I was younger and still naive enough to think that maybe someday we'd be able to live on another one haha. I think we have an awful lot going on here on Earth.
Yes, I agree we do! Astronomers detected building blocks of life in a system 455 light years away!

Seems pretty useless from a practical standpoint, but the information about other planets is interesting nonetheless. There's a planet where shards of glass rain sideways at 4500 MPH in 2000 degree weather...you can't make this stuff up!
They have gathered so much information we don't even know about! The different planet Uranus rotates sideways  and rolls instead of spinning like the other planets!
It's crazy, right? Venus actually rotates clockwise and it the only planet to do so. It's also not on a tilt in the way Earth is, so it has no seasons.
Yes, so interesting, very hot planet!  5.5 hours a day when the earth first formed.  Wouldn't get as much done.
Well, luckily it's done forming and now it the densest planet in the solar system. It's odd to think that at the center of it is a solid core of iron when all we see is land and ice!
Yes it is. The earth and the moon causes ocean tides. I love to walk the beach at night looking at the moon. Its so relaxing. In the Virgin Islands the stars are unbelievable!
Is that so? I bet there's not much light pollution the way there is in more developed areas; heck, over 80% of Earth's natural forests have already been destroyed.
That's upsetting! I love nature and old trees that been around for 100 years  Wow, the earth will be helium free by the end of the 21st century!
It's amazing how much damage humans have done in such a short amount of time. If Earth's entire history was 24 hours, human existence would only be 1 minute and 17 seconds long!
I was thinking about that! Our time here is so short. The United Nations has appointed an ambassador to extraterrestrials in case they make contact. I wonder if they will tell us?
We're so small in the context of the universe that it seems impossible; did you know that the sun is only a billionth the size of the biggest star in our galaxy?
Oh my that's unbelievable!! A lightening bolt is about 5x hotter than the surface of the sun!
That's incredible, especially when you consider that the sun produces enough energy in one second to meet the energy needs of earth for half a million years.
I know for a half a million years!! The sun is white but because of atmospheric scattering it looks yellow.
No matter what color is, it's absolutely huge compared to the rest of the solar system--it accounts for about 99.86% of the total mass.
That's true Jupiter has a moon called ganymede. Good chat!!
Yes, if it orbited the sun instead, its size would make it a planet.
Yes, have a good night!
Do you enjoy any type of hobbies or entertainment?
I do but I am not passionate about any of them. I really just like spending time with my family as my hobby... What about you, do you have any hobbies?
I personally enjoy traveling with family. How about you?
I do like to travel with my family. We like to go to hotels with pools, like the Wisconsin Dells. Where have you been that is fun?
I have traveled throughout japan and man was it expensive. Did you know all of japan's highways are tolls so traveling cross country alone is already $300
I did not. That's a lot of money to spend on tolls. Did you like Japan?

Japan was definitely a unique experience in a different culture. Also it was very convenient to move around, unlike for instance Mackinac island, which has banned motorized vehicles for over a 100 years
I think I would enjoy a society without motorized vehicles... Especially on the beauiful Mackinac Island. The homes and vegitation on that island are just beautiful!

That would definitely be a defining aspect of Mackinac Island, but transpiration would definitely be inconvenient. Another such case is Iceland which lacks a public rail services so to move between major towns, people need to use domestic flights
The King Kalakaua could have used that. He was the first king to travel around the world.
Do you prefer to travel by foot, bike, train, boat, plane, or other?
I like car, unless it is far, then plane. But I hate traveling by plane. That turbulance is too much for me.
Then do you choose to rather travel domestically rather than internationally?
I will travel internationally, I have been to mexico but nothing else. I am planning a trip to Ireland in the upcoming year. Have you been?
I don't have any plans at this moment for traveling, but I am considering going to some concerts.  Do you enjoy music and concerts?
I do like concerts. Which ones are you thinking about going to?
I am planning to go to one by Joe hisaishi, but I also want to try going to a concert held at an ancient roman amphitheatre someday as well
That would be fun. There's an ancient roman amphitheatre in Croatia! You should go there.
Yes I would like to someday. I would also like to go to concerts by amazing artists like linkin park. They were so successful that they played 324 concerts in 2001 alone
That's a long time on the road. Do you think you would be able to make it that long on the road?

I probably could not, but I would definitely like to see at least one. I mean they were probably successful for a good reason, unlike the creed concert that was so bad that 4 concerts got filed lawsuits against.
I remember that! Nice chatting with you!
Hi, how are you? do you like the radio?
Yea, it's pretty cool how sound is produce through electromagnetic energy waves through space
yes, it is a great invention. i think it has helped many people around the world get their news and maybe get educated.
Yea, in Finland they even have a new program in classical latin called Nuntii Latini
I guess they have dedicated fans because that has been around for decades.
Apparently, I heard dedicated fans of classic radio dramas can listen to them online for free
there are some great dramas out there. i think the history of entertainment tells a lot about the stories we see now on tv
What's pretty cool is you can pick up Jupiter's radio storms on am radio, I wonder what frequency you have to tune to
i dont know. i dont know what they would sound like so i couldnt recognize them. strange.
Not as strange as the President of Indonesia releasing 3 pop albums while in office lol
I guess he had a yearning to be heard. He needed his voice to be acknowledged. Plus he wanted the cash.
Maybe but JFK, Washington, and Jefferson were the 3 wealthiest presidents and they never released any albums
Yes, JFK has his father's rum money. And the two others owned heaps of land. JFK has the look of a star but not the singing voice. his mistress did though.
I wonder if the first president of zimbabwe was rich, maybe he sold bananas since they called him President Banana
Perhaps given that nickname for a reason
Perhaps. Did you know the runner up in the presidential election became vice president until 1805?
that was an odd system. maybe the vp had more power then? now its a ceremonial position for the most part. i would not want it.
Sounds like way too much stress, I'd imagine the vice president and president probably hated each other
Yes, they probably were not on the same page and little got accomplished. Now it is a pointless position. Little real authority. Anyway, nice chat!
You too. I'm gonna go look up more info about the man who sold the Eiffel Tower twice
That man was a genius salesman. Have a good night!
thanks, you too
The telephone is a great invention,
Absolutely!  Love the telephone!
It makes life a lot more easier, I can check the mail, call and even watch funny videos just by using my phone
An iphone has more computing power than the entire us nuclear icbm deterrent.
That is kind of scary I own an iphone, didnt know I was packing so much power in my front pocket
Yeah,  better be careful!  people use phones for eveything now,  Ive seen in movies they attach it to bombs and stuff.
Powerful weapons if used in the wrong hands, scary since everyone has access to them
Yeah, seriously.   I hear there's a company that will donate a day of clean water for every minute you don't use your phone!
That is really admirable, donating water to children in need, an awesome campaign
Yeah great thing to do,  water is essential.
It is, just like phones have also become essential in our lives, interesting fact about phonebooks, its impossible to separate two of them with their pages fully overlapped
lol I never tried but I believe you. Do you like clothing?  Did you know polo shirts were actually meant for tennis players?
I didnt know that, always thought it was meant for the polo sport or maybe that the Polo brand created them
Same here,  yeah a tennis player created them
I looks like polo player took the credit then, did you hear about the cultural revolution in China?
No I havent whats that about?
Basically the more clothes you wore the better you looked to others.
Oh my,  that seems uncomfotable lol At least they are warm though,  I think china gets cold.  Must spend a lot of time doing laundry lol
I know right, I don't think that's a thing anymore but it doesnt seem like a comfortable thing
Yeah maybe,  every culture has its own style. Its interesting.
I agree, different cultures and different customs thats what makes life interesting, just like this chat, thanks for your time
Thanks,  its been a great conversation,  have a good one.
Hi. Do you like comedy movies?
I love comedy movies, especially bromantic comedies like pineapple express
I like that they mostly have happy endings.
for sure lol, have you seen kung fu hustle?
I haven't, have you?
I have not either, I may want to see it. Bill  Murray says it is comedy gold, trying to get other opinions
He's probably a good judge of what's funny! Some of the first movies ever were comedies.
For sure. Did you ever watch whose line is it anyways?
I did! It's a pretty funny show!
I guess Ryan stiles dropped out of school to pursue comedy, it was the right move. dude is hilarious!
Definitely! Dean Martin chose comedy instead of law school!
That is crazy, I am sure he is making more money now than law school would have paid him in his career! Do you have a favorite bromantic comedy?
I like the hangover series!
Me too, I saw all of them in theaters, so funny!
Have you seen Harold & Kumar?
I love those movies, I have never been to white castle though, do you like them?
I like the movies, but not the hamburgers. Did you ever watch 3rd Rock From the Sun?
I used to watch it but never understood it, was it good?
It beat Seinfeld, and Friends for a Golden Globe award. I liked Friends a lot better, though!
I was all about Seinfeld, i cant believe that
I was shocked, too! Nice talking to you! Have a great rest of your night!
Hi there! So have you heard about the play Cry it Out? Not sure if you know but that is a parenting technique popular with some.
I havnt heard of it what is it about.
It's basically about choices in child rearing, like social circles and extreme costs of raising kids and keeping up with life.
I can certainly relate to all that. I have three kids.
I can as well. No easy task. The woman that writes the plays speaks of how pre-kids she never thought about what parents go through. Her name is Metzler. She has written for TV too/
I might have to check that out. May be able to get some pointers.
Ha! She says having a baby changed her and made her look at choices like going back to work parents have.
Well that is true I guess. Having kids changes everything.
It does! So moving to another topic, I LOVE cars!  The model T was the first cars available to the masses.
I love cars as well. did you know that cadillac was actually named after a frednch explorer who founded detroit.
Nope, did not know, that's cool! Did you know the trunk of the car is called the trunk because they used to have wooden trunks on the back?
Wonder why old henry ford didnt think about people needing a place to put their stuff when he made the model t
No kidding! So, now onto other tech, TV is pretty amazing. I am familiar with the show Thomas about the train, but had no idea Ring Starr narrated it.
i was unaware of that as well. My son loves thomas though.
Did you know there have been over 750 episodes of Pokemon? Enough for 50 a year for 16 years!!
Thats just crazy. I never got the pokemon thing. Guess That is something for the younger generations.
So-so, it's been around for a long time. I am surprised with the choices on TV that Netflix is so popular and has over 130 million subscribers.
I really like netflix. I think its because you can pause and rewind and choose exactly what you want to watch when you want to.
Agreed, although I wish they got new movies sooner. Hard to believe Netflix takes 33% of all bandwidth in North America from 9 pm to 12 am! Good talking to you.
that is pretty amazing considering all the other content that is available on the internet.
yes. We have a lot of choices.
Do you follow the NFL?
I sometimes follow the NFL. i try to watch the superbowl. You?
Same here, Im a fan of the game but usually don't have any time to watch it.
what do you think of the rules about women playing?
I think that woman are at a disadvantage.
I dont think women can gain muscle in the way they would need to.
Yeah what are your thoughts on the Saints and the rule they have against cheerleaders?
I think it is sexist and outdated. who cares if the cheerleaders eat in the same restaurant as the players?
I agree who cares and if you dont want players and cheerleaders getting together then it should apply to both and if a cheerleader is having a meal with friends/family then the player should leave
Use the tracking chips to know where the players are and this problem could be avoided.
What are your thoughts on those tracking chips? I hear the football has one as well
A good way to track players for strategy. maybe help prevent injuries.
Could be, there is a lot of controversy concerning brain damage and injuries in players, its sad when you think about it, when you think about them
Yes, it is a tragedy. many players end up broke, and lose their minds as well. player safety is key.
I agree so do you have a favorite team? mine is the Packers.
I like the bay area teams. they did not do well this year though.
They did now, interesting but the team is community owned, its a not for profit team
Yeah, it is the only one in the league that is owned by a city govt.
D you know how they got their name? its actually a really interesting story
I dont know. how did they get their name?
Because of an Indian packing company called Green Bay Packers, they paid for the team's uniforms and so they named the team after the company. Anyways its been great chatting with you
Yes, i enjoyed chatting! Have a good nigh!
You have a great night as well my friend.
Hi, are you a basketball fan?
Yes! I went to University of Kentucky!
Good deal. Did you know that Lebron James and Stephen Curry were both born in Akron Ohio?
That is neat. I love it that Tim Duncan of the Spurs stayed in college 4 years instead of going into the nba. That is unheard of today!
That was really smart. You never know in sports if you are going to have a short career. He made sure he had something to fall back on.
True! Did you know that shooting granny style is the best technique. But everyone feels like it looks ridiculous so they won't do it.
I didn't know that. But I do know that that was the only way I could shoot a free throw when I was young.
Me too! do you like Stephen Curry?
I don't know much about him, but I guess he pretty good.
He is pretty amazing. He was the star of the golden state warriors in 201.
Yes. I was reading that he was the first player to win the MVP by a unanimous vote.
He is that good! Curry is currently signed with Under Armour because Nike had such a bad pitch.
I say good for Under Armour. Nike has had it their way for a long time. I like Under Armour products.
I agree!!!
Changing the subject a little. The dutch are creating a commuter bus that can travel 160 miles per hour.
That is cool. Have you ever been to Mackinac island?
No I haven't where is it, and have you been there?
I haven't but I have relatives that live close. Everything is horse drawn carriages or you can take a bike.
So they don't allow motorized vehicles at all?
Nope. Not at all! I kind of like that. It makes the island so peaceful!
It would be nice. I know I like to hike in the desert and get away from all the sounds of the city.
Yes It would.
The only problem is I don't guess you can stop the occasional airplane from flying over.
Good talking to you.
do you like jazz music?
I sure do. Did you know CLint Eastwood is also a huge fan?
Yes and he also loves the piano too
Yes. A woman in harlem hosts free concerts in her apartment every day
Yes for 20 years now and many people stop by there
Yeah. Do you know who has the best jazz orchestra in the world?
Yes that is Pakistan, strange a bit but good for them
I know. Do you know why trumpeters have a goatee?
Yes because it is more comfortable when they play
Yes. Do you like Pixar?
I sure do, they also have a room where only celebrities are allowed in
Yeah. Did you know RObin Williams was the voice of Aladdin?
Yes and he started that trend of celebrities doing voices
Yeah. Did you know LeBron is the only one that makes more than JUdge Judy?
Yeah. Carol Burnett was the first celebrity on Sesame Street
Yeah. Did you know Texas elected their first female governor when some others statements had not even ratified the amendment?
Yeah. DO you know the songs Come Together by the Beatles?
Yes it was written for a California Governor's campaign in 1969.
Yeah. Do you know where Schwarzenegger lived when he was governor?
Not in Sacramento, he travelled everyday there though
Yes and he used a private jet every day
Hello , How are you doing.
Hello there, I am well thank you.  Do you watch much basketball?
Yeah I do sometimes. Mostly in the playoffs. I havent really watched much this year though.
I mostly just follow my local team, which has been really good this season so far, they are best in the league.
Oh yeah, college or pros. Were you aware that the only head coach in kansas University history with a losing record is james naismith. The inventor of basketball.
Wow, that is a very impressive program.  I wonder what Mr. Naismith would think of the game today?
I would say he would be surprised at the athletic ability of the players these days. I doubt this is what he really imagined. Not to say he would be disappointed.
Yeah I think he would be most impressed by the amount and style of dunking that happens today.
I know it impresses me a lot. Another fun fact is that in 39 out of the 50 states. The highest played employee is a college football or basketball coach. Thats just crazy.
That is crazy, not to say that those jobs aren't important but that just blows my mind.
Yeah mine to. I have always like playing basketball. Never been great at it , but I enjoy playing.
Yeah that used to be my go to sport when I was a kid.  I used to tape all of the dunk contests.  I used to love Larry Johnson and Shawn Kemp.
A hornets fan huh. I liked the heat when I was a kid. I liked that crossover Tim Hardaway did. Until Allen Iverson came to the league then he was my favorite.
Heck yeah Tim Hardaway was awesome, I remember watching him on the Warriors.  Iverson was awesome too, he got the best of my team back in 2001, but, I think we will be back there this year.
I haven't really followed it much this year. Are they doing pretty well.
Yeah the Bucks, they are first place in the whole league, I really hope we can make the finals, I have never seen it in my lifetime.
Yeah Giannis is pretty good. i think he is better than Lebron, at least at this stage in their careers.
Yeah Giannis has been a diamond in the rough and turned this franchise around since he has been here.  I like Lebron, he has done so much, but I think it's Giannis's time.

I think Lebron is a great player, I just hate it how he has done cleveland. I think he should have stayed there his whole career and brought them a bunch of championships. It would have been a great story.
Yeah if he would've done like Dirk and the Mavs, imagine how many titles, and yeah we would've gone down as Clevelands biggest hero.
It is kind of sad what he has done. He basically said forget my hometown, just to go get a couple more championships that he probably could have got anyway.

Yeah I don't like when players leave a team just to get a ring.  If you want to do it right, play for one team, and do enough to make it happen while you're there. It was nice talking with you today, I hope you have a good day.
Hello! I hope today we can have a good discussion about football and religion, and how in some cases they have merged.
I think Brady is looking for a way to stay relevant and this spirituality through football is a bit ridiculous.
Honestly, same. When Daniel Wann said "sports might bring people together better than religion" I honestly scoffed at how absurd that statement is.
If anything I think that the idea of sports tends to make people more divisive. It is crazy how bitter and competitive people get about teams.
Same, if I would agree with anyone from these articles I would agree with Bob Ryan because he's skeptical about it - as he should be!
I wonder if people would be as apt to follow brady if he was losing more than he was winning.
I doubt it, which is funny seeing as when it's about religion, people will follow through almost anything.
I wonder if he is setting it up to have some sort of cult or MLM stuff once he is finally too old play anymore.
To be honest that would be pretty cool. I enjoy learning about cults, they're interesting. I was surprised when I read the NFL has no rule against female players!
That sure is suprising considering how male dominated the sport is.
Honestly, yeah. Did you see about girls being allowed into Boy Scouts? Gets me pretty riled up lol. Did you see that it used to be required to read from a bible in the U.S?
I know that it was commonly used as reading curriculum. It was an easily accessible book and quite a challenging read.
I wish they still had classes in high school at least! Not forced, but optional.. Did you read that Iowa's locker room for visiting football teams is completely pink??? That cracked me up.
That does seem like something Iowa would do. They are quite into razzing other players from opposite teams.
Really? I don't know much about them honestly... What do you know?
There is a huge rivalry between the two teams from the main Iowa colleges. Either you are a hawkeye fan or an UN of I fan. They are as bad as packers and vikings fans
Ahh... It's like that down here in Alabama!! Did you see the average NFL game only has 11 minutes of live game-play?
The rest of the time must be spent on huddles and waiting for the snap. I wonder if other forms of football have more action time.
Yeah, that seems kinda silly to me to waste all that time..
It really does. I wonder if there was more time to the cumberland game where they set the high score record.
What was that all about? The cumberland game?
Cumberland completely whupped Georgia back at the beginning of the century. It was 222-0. I mean at some point you just need to give up.
D a n g that's crazy. Well thanks for the great conversation!
Yes it was a nice chat.
Hi there, do you enjoy poetry?
No I really don't.I don't understand it and find it boring.
Oh I see. Some of them can be cool though, like that poem that when read normally is depressing and vice versa
there is a 274 line poem called the chaos, i am assuming becaus it has irregularly pronounced words
I would assume so too. THe Javanese alphabet too, if recited in order it forms a poem
the vikings were warrior poets. lol what the heck? did they just shout poetry at the enemy ?
Hahaha maybe that is how they fought. Allan Poe received only $9 for his poem The Raven. Not is is priceless
isn't that always the way? things don't become priceless until the person is dead. baltimore must be the place for poetry! first edgar allen poe and also tupac
Yeah it seems that way. On another topic, do you like dogs?
Lol these really arent my favorite subjects. I am not a dog fan.
Oh I see. But just for curiosity, they have 12 blood types, way more than we do
they can also reason better than chimps
Seem lie it since they understand pointing, same as elephants
they enjoy solving a problem
Yeah that too. Even Google has declared itself as a dog company
im guessing with that they allow employees to bring dogs to work? I can't ever figure out what makes them a dog compnay
Well maybe and they have it in their code of conduct that they are a dog company
russia must really be into dogs they have a tomb of the unknown dog AND some of their dogs have learned to use the subway
Wow that is impressive. For a long time I thought that dogs were colorblind but apprently they just do not see as many colors as we do
and they can learn over 1000 words. I guess thats why they make them service dogs
Yeah, it makes sense. Nice chat
I never knew that ringo starr narrated some episodes of thomas the thank engine.
Yes.     Funny that he was the more mild Narrator, compared to George Carlin and Alec Baldwin
I also can't believe there are that many pokemon episodes. My son used to watch these all the time as a kid.
I heard it was something like sixteen years worth!
it's been around so long. I can't believe it's still even popular to this day!
At least Pokemon was not around in the black and white television days!
In your country, do people call the sport soccer or football?
Football.     It is amazing so many different games like Australian football also use the same name!
I agree! I never even knew there was such a thing as Austailian or Canadian football!
True.    One version I just learned about is Gaelic football
what is that?
Gaelic indicates an Irish game, 15 players somewhat similar to rugby football.
i never knew that. you're really smart! it's crazy how much football players make these days!
Yes.    In the 1960's top bowlers made twice as much as top football stars
That's unbelievable!
Then again, salaries all over are huge.    Look at 2011 superhero film Thor!
I'm a huge fan of superhero movies. I really liked Thor. Chris Hemsworth was a good actor in it.
i did not know that Kenneth Branagh was such a good director!
I also enjoyed Natalie Portman in it. She's one of my favorite actresses.
I prefer Rene Russo's acting in the film.
Both were really good, as was Anthony Hopikins!

DO you still use a landline ?

No.  In my opinion, the landline is going extinct.  Growing up my grandparents had a multi-party line.  My parents had a landline.  I killed the landline once cellular was cost effective.  Now cellphones are small computers that do so much more than landlines.
Yeah, an IPhone has more computing power than a mainframe of the 60s. But data still travels best in cables.

Even on cellular networks, it still travels via cable, except for the last leg.  Could you imagine the atmospheric distortion of the signal if data was transmitted from the east to west coast solely via the airways?
We would be still at the era of ham radios and telegram. There would be less pictures.
Less pictures and more garbled messages.  Imagine how YouTube videos would look with atmospheric distortion; probably like the picture on old time TVs with rabbit ear antennas?
Youtube would be like a TV station, showing only clip to everyone at the same time. I think it would be less popular.
True.  Do you subscribe to any YouTube channels or follow any YouTube celebrities?
I subscribe to some educational channels. But I don't follow any celebrities, but I hear of them often.

Given that YouTube is accessible to anyone with a computer, being a star has nothing to do with how good your Hollywood agent is and more with establishing a populist following.
It is more diverse but celebrities still have an advantage on Youtube, being a search engine, popular results get more visibility.

Agreed.  It is a bit art / a bit science in figuring out how to get your videos promoted in the search results.  Or, hire an expert who will flood your videos with fictional views to promote its popularity.  But established names also help. Judge Judy makes $123K per TV episode; with that amount of draw, her YouTube channel can't help but be a success.
Do you think 123 000 $ per episode is too much for her ?

I do not watch her, so I cannot judge.  It is one of the few areas where free market economics still reigns.  So, if they feel she's worth it, then it's not my place to judge.  But that type of draw opens up other markets.  For example, Carol Burnett was the first celeb on Sesame Street.
It was the 70s, she was the star at that time, it makes sense. I wonder if youtube will have a lasting impact on the star system or this Youtubers thing is just a phase.
